Class Overview

  • By the end of this class, you should:
    • Be comfortable in working with R, including most common geospatial functions
    • Have a good sense of where R is headed as a language
    • Know where to look when dont know how to do something
    • Be:
      • Using R as part of a reproducible workflow
      • OR at least be sold on the tenets of reproducibility
  • Course approach
    • Flipped model and emphasis on problem solving
      • Programming should be fun! (or at least intriguing)
    • Classroom and office hours as help sessions

Getting Set Up

  • Get yourself a GitHub account, if you havent
  • Send us your GitHub name
  • Install git on your local computer(s)
  • Set up your personal access token
  • Install the geospaar library
  • Learn how to create your own github repo under the @agroimpacts/geog246346 team
